### 2023
| Trial Corpus | Patient Notes |
|---|---|
375,000+ trials — May 8, 2023 snapshot | 50 STRCUTURED questionaries |

```bash 
mkdir -p data/synthetic/trials/TREC_2023
mkdir -p data/synthetic/patients/TREC_2023
mkdir -p data/synthetic/eval/TREC_2023

# Trials 
# May 8, 2023 snapshot 

for i in $(seq 0 5); do 
     wget https://www.trec-cds.org/2023_data/ClinicalTrials.2023-05-08.trials${i}.zip -O data/synthetic/trials/TREC_2023/ClinicalTrials.2023-05-08.trials${i}.zip

     unzip data/synthetic/trials/TREC_2023/ClinicalTrials.2023-05-08.trials${i}.zip -d data/synthetic/trials/TREC_2023/
done


#Includes 50 new topics not included in 2021 nor 2022
# The 2021 and 2022 topics had a very different structure (free-text narratives along the lines of a case report or electronic health record note)
# The topics for the track consist of synthetic patient descriptions based on questionnaire templates.
# Each row represents one entry (i.e one question based on a disease treat), the second dield is the patient response to it
wget https://www.trec-cds.org/topics2023.xml -O data/synthetic/patients/TREC_2023/topics2023.xml

# same as before
wget https://trec.nist.gov/data/trials/qrels2022.txt -O data/synthetic/eval/TREC_2023/qrels2023.txt

```

